{
  "message": "Add secret type support for UDOs\n\nUser-defined operators in packages can now declare parameters with the\n`secret` type to ensure that secret values are properly handled as secret\nexpressions. Previously, you could only declare operator parameters as\nfield paths or untyped. This change enables the package system to recognize\nand properly validate that only secret expressions (created with the\nsecret() function) are passed to these parameters.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "cf5880a094503eedd1da530761aa90828e76ed4d",
      "filename": "changelog/unreleased/secret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md",
      "status": "added",
      "additions": 19,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 19,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/blob/47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a/changelog%2Funreleased%2Fsecret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/raw/47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a/changelog%2Funreleased%2Fsecret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/tenzir/contents/changelog%2Funreleased%2Fsecret-type-support-for-user-defined-operator-parameters.md?ref=47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a",
      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@\n+---\n+title: Secret type support for user-defined operator parameters\n+type: bugfix\n+authors:\n+  - mavam\n+  - claude\n+pr: 5752\n+created: 2026-02-12T17:26:03.709677Z\n+---\n+\n+User-defined operators in packages can now declare parameters with the `secret` type to ensure that secret values are properly handled as secret expressions:\n+\n+```\n+args:\n+  positional:\n+    - name: api_key\n+      type: secret\n+      description: \"API key to use for authentication\"\n+```"
    },
    {
      "sha": "d0873f0c1fb32d7e96988606c587d7a8e48742e5",
      "filename": "libtenzir/src/package.cpp",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 3,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 3,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/blob/47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Fpackage.cpp",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/raw/47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Fpackage.cpp",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/tenzir/contents/libtenzir%2Fsrc%2Fpackage.cpp?ref=47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a",
      "patch": "@@ -439,6 +439,9 @@ auto parse_parameter_value_type(const package_operator_parameter& param,\n   if (not param.type || is_field_path_type(param)) {\n     return std::optional<type>{};\n   }\n+  if (*param.type == \"secret\") {\n+    return std::optional<type>{type{secret_type{}}};\n+  }\n   // Using the legacy parser here because it is convenient.\n   // We will eventually add support for user defined operators in TQL itself and\n   // deprecate this approach, so it does not make sense to refactor the tql2"
    },
    {
      "sha": "3cb61c4af02879b92cd0ab12abe962a3d4d7b7bb",
      "filename": "test-legacy/inputs/package-roots/udo-args/argspkg/operators/typed_named_secret.tql",
      "status": "added",
      "additions": 11,
      "deletions": 0,
      "changes": 11,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/blob/47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a/test-legacy%2Finputs%2Fpackage-roots%2Fudo-args%2Fargspkg%2Foperators%2Ftyped_named_secret.tql",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/tenzir/tenzir/raw/47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a/test-legacy%2Finputs%2Fpackage-roots%2Fudo-args%2Fargspkg%2Foperators%2Ftyped_named_secret.tql",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tenzir/tenzir/contents/test-legacy%2Finputs%2Fpackage-roots%2Fudo-args%2Fargspkg%2Foperators%2Ftyped_named_secret.tql?ref=47e590043e542ceb8aacd04962a9b1c4887f414a",
      "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,11 @@\n+---\n+description: \"Accept a named argument that is declared as secret\"\n+args:\n+  named:\n+    - name: value\n+      type: secret\n+      description: \"Must be a secret expression\"\n+---\n+\n+operator = \"typed_named_secret\"\n+value = $value"
    },
